article.headline: High Point 66, N.C.-Asheville 62
article.story: HIGH POINT, N.C. -- Eugene Harris scored 15 points on five 3-pointers to lead High Point to a 66-62 win over UNC-Asheville on Monday night for its third win in a row. Harris, the Big South Conference's active leader with 246 3-pointers, was 5-for-10 from behind the arc. Nick Barbour added 14 points and Tehran Cox had 10. Cruz Daniels, who has averaged 11 points and 10 rebounds in the past four games, had 13 points and 11 rebounds for the Flames (7-6, 3-1 Big South Conference). The Flames improved to 6-0 at home this season despite committing 24 turnovers. J.P. Primm and John Williams scored 14 points each for the Bulldogs (3-10, 1-2) who lost their fourth straight. D.J. Cunningham added 13 points and 12 rebounds for UNC-Asheville. The Bulldogs scored 48 points in the paint to keep it close.
